Compute descriptive statistics on columns of a data frame

descriptives.Rd

The user can specify an unlimited number of functions to evaluate and the types of data that each set of functions will be applied to (including the default; see "Details").

descriptives(
    data,
    f_all = NULL,
    f_numeric = NULL,
    numeric_types = "numeric",
    f_categorical = NULL,
    categorical_types = "factor",
    f_other = NULL,
    useNA = c("ifany", "no", "always"),
    round = 2,
    na_string = "(missing)"
)

Arguments

data

A base::data.frame.
f_all

A base::list of functions to evaluate on all columns.
f_numeric

A base::list of functions to evaluate on numeric_types columns.
numeric_types

Character vector of data types that should be evaluated by f_numeric.
f_categorical

A base::list of functions to evaluate on categorical_types columns.
categorical_types

Character vector of data types that should be evaluated by f_categorical.
f_other

A base::list of functions to evaluate on remaining columns.
useNA

See base::table for details. Defaults to "ifany".
round

Digit to round numeric data. Defaults to 2.
na_string

String to fill in NA names.

Details

The min, max, median, iqr, mean, sd are automatically computed for numeric data and table, prop.table*100 for categorical data. The sample size, number of missing values, number of nonmissing values, the number of unique values, the class are automatically computed on all columns.

Value

A tibble::tibble with the following columns:

  • column: Position/index of the input dataset

  • column_name: Label of the column

  • type: Set of column types function was applied to

  • key: Name of function that was evaluated

  • value_order: Position of the value within the function result

  • value_name: Label extracted from the result with base::names

  • value_num: Numeric results

  • value_chr: Non-numeric results

  • value_combo: Output combined with rounding applied to numeric values

Examples

#Default
heart_disease %>%
    descriptives()
#> # A tibble: 111 x 9
#>    column column_name type  key   value_order value_name value_num value_chr
#>     <int> <chr>       <chr> <chr>       <int> <chr>          <dbl> <chr>    
#>  1      1 Age         all   avai…           1 NA             303   NA       
#>  2      1 Age         all   class           1 NA              NA   numeric  
#>  3      1 Age         all   leng…           1 NA             303   NA       
#>  4      1 Age         all   miss…           1 NA               0   NA       
#>  5      1 Age         all   uniq…           1 NA              41   NA       
#>  6      1 Age         nume… iqr             1 NA              13   NA       
#>  7      1 Age         nume… max             1 NA              77   NA       
#>  8      1 Age         nume… mean            1 NA              54.4 NA       
#>  9      1 Age         nume… medi…           1 NA              56   NA       
#> 10      1 Age         nume… min             1 NA              29   NA       
#> # … with 101 more rows, and 1 more variable: value_combo <chr>

#Allow logicals as categorical
heart_disease %>%
    descriptives(
        categorical_types = c("logical", "factor")
    )
#> # A tibble: 117 x 9
#>    column column_name type  key   value_order value_name value_num value_chr
#>     <int> <chr>       <chr> <chr>       <int> <chr>          <dbl> <chr>    
#>  1      1 Age         all   avai…           1 NA             303   NA       
#>  2      1 Age         all   class           1 NA              NA   numeric  
#>  3      1 Age         all   leng…           1 NA             303   NA       
#>  4      1 Age         all   miss…           1 NA               0   NA       
#>  5      1 Age         all   uniq…           1 NA              41   NA       
#>  6      1 Age         nume… iqr             1 NA              13   NA       
#>  7      1 Age         nume… max             1 NA              77   NA       
#>  8      1 Age         nume… mean            1 NA              54.4 NA       
#>  9      1 Age         nume… medi…           1 NA              56   NA       
#> 10      1 Age         nume… min             1 NA              29   NA       
#> # … with 107 more rows, and 1 more variable: value_combo <chr>

#Only apply "other" functions to numeric types
heart_disease %>%
    descriptives(
        numeric_types = NULL
    )
#> # A tibble: 75 x 9
#>    column column_name type  key   value_order value_name value_num value_chr
#>     <int> <chr>       <chr> <chr>       <int> <chr>          <dbl> <chr>    
#>  1      1 Age         all   avai…           1 NA               303 NA       
#>  2      1 Age         all   class           1 NA                NA numeric  
#>  3      1 Age         all   leng…           1 NA               303 NA       
#>  4      1 Age         all   miss…           1 NA                 0 NA       
#>  5      1 Age         all   uniq…           1 NA                41 NA       
#>  6      2 Sex         all   avai…           1 NA               303 NA       
#>  7      2 Sex         all   class           1 NA                NA factor   
#>  8      2 Sex         all   leng…           1 NA               303 NA       
#>  9      2 Sex         all   miss…           1 NA                 0 NA       
#> 10      2 Sex         all   uniq…           1 NA                 2 NA       
#> # … with 65 more rows, and 1 more variable: value_combo <chr>

#Compute a custom function
heart_disease %>%
    descriptives(
        f_numeric =
            list(
                cv = function(x) sd(x, na.rm = TRUE)/mean(x, na.rm = TRUE)
            )
    )
#> # A tibble: 115 x 9
#>    column column_name type  key   value_order value_name value_num value_chr
#>     <int> <chr>       <chr> <chr>       <int> <chr>          <dbl> <chr>    
#>  1      1 Age         all   avai…           1 NA           303     NA       
#>  2      1 Age         all   class           1 NA            NA     numeric  
#>  3      1 Age         all   leng…           1 NA           303     NA       
#>  4      1 Age         all   miss…           1 NA             0     NA       
#>  5      1 Age         all   uniq…           1 NA            41     NA       
#>  6      1 Age         nume… cv              1 NA             0.166 NA       
#>  7      1 Age         nume… iqr             1 NA            13     NA       
#>  8      1 Age         nume… max             1 NA            77     NA       
#>  9      1 Age         nume… mean            1 NA            54.4   NA       
#> 10      1 Age         nume… medi…           1 NA            56     NA       
#> # … with 105 more rows, and 1 more variable: value_combo <chr>
